## Quick Start

### 1. Install CLI (Python)
Ensure you have [uv](https://github.com/astral-sh/uv) installed.
```bash
git clone https://github.com/Adanato/obsidian_2_anki
cd obsidian_2_anki
uv sync
```

### 2. Install Plugin (Optional)
Download `main.js`, `manifest.json`, `styles.css` from [Releases](https://github.com/Adanato/obsidian_2_anki/releases) and place in `.obsidian/plugins/obsidian-2-anki`.

### 3. Initialize & Sync
```bash
uv run arete init   # Set up your vault path
uv run arete sync   # First sync (will scan and link cards)
```

## Key Features
- ‚ö° **Fast**: SQLite caching skips unchanged files, making syncs near-instant.
- üßπ **Prune Mode**: Automatically removes cards from Anki that you've deleted in Obsidian.
- ü©π **Self-Healing**: Fixes duplicate IDs or broken links automatically.
- üìê **MathJax/LaTeX**: Native protection for complex mathematical notation.
- üì∏ **Media Support**: Full synchronization of local images and attachments.
- üíª **WSL Friendly**: Specialized bridge for Windows Subsystem for Linux users.

